description: This file implements the container object functions for the Bwsp Site Creator Object, including creation, removal, object enrollment, and initialization. It defines how the object is constructed, destroyed, and set up within the system, including interface setup and configuration.

classes.name: BWSP_SITE_CREATOR_OBJECT
classes.description: Structural representation of the Bwsp Site Creator Object, containing properties and function pointers for object lifecycle management.

methods.name: ANSC_HANDLE BwspScoCreate(ANSC_HANDLE hContainerContext,ANSC_HANDLE hOwnerContext,ANSC_HANDLE hAnscReserved)
methods.description: Constructs and initializes a new Bwsp Site Creator Object, setting core properties and function pointers.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS BwspScoRemove(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Destroys the Bwsp Site Creator Object, freeing associated resources.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS BwspScoEnrollObjects(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Enroller method that allocates and sets up required interface objects for the Bwsp Site Creator Object.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS BwspScoInitialize(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Initializes the Bwsp Site Creator Object, setting default property values and function pointers.
